Following the opening of its West Africa office in Ghana earlier this week, Johnson & Johnson today announced the further expansion of its operations in Africa with the launch of a new office in Nairobi, Kenya.&nbsp;"The opening of the new Johnson & Johnson office will play a major role in supporting our goal of helping to improve the quality of and access to healthcare in the region, while showcasing a model that can be replicated across Africa," said Vittorio Sereni, Country Manager of the Johnson & Johnson office in Nairobi. Read more.&nbsp;